ceef4b8524a319a23cB5e9f3936" itemprop=3D"StoryLink" itemscope=3D"itemscope"=
 target=3D"_blank" style=3D"color: #000000; text-decoration: none !importan=
t; border-bottom-width: 1px; border-bottom-color: #000000; border-bottom-st=
yle: solid; background-color: #ccc;">  talked a few times</a> over the year=
s about the mysterious Tesla Inc. lawyer=C2=A0whose court-mandated job is t=
o review Elon Musk=E2=80=99s draft tweets that might be material to Tesla s=
hareholders. In theory, Musk has to show his tweets to this lawyer, and if =
the lawyer says =E2=80=9Cthis is material and misleading,=E2=80=9D Musk is =
supposed to not tweet it. In practice =E2=80=A6=C2=A0really? Musk is a vola=
tile and demanding boss who tweets impulsively at all hours and, what, you=
=E2=80=99re going to stop him? You=E2=80=99re not going to stop him. Terrib=
le job. I don=E2=80=99t think anyone has <a href=3D"https://link.mail.bloom=
bergbusiness.com/click/33930957.258410/aHR0cHM6Ly93d3cuYmxvb21iZXJnLmNvbS9v=
cGluaW9uL25ld3NsZXR0ZXJzLzIwMTktMDItMjAvbW9uZXktc3R1ZmYtZWxvbi1tdXNrLWNhbi1=
0LWhlbHAtaGltc2VsZj9jbXBpZD1CQkQwMTA4MjRfTU9ORVlTVFVGRiZ1dG1fbWVkaXVtPWVtYW=
