mV5c3R1ZmY/607f07ceef4b8524a319a23cBb8112ece" itemprop=3D"StoryLink" itemsc=
ope=3D"itemscope" target=3D"_blank" style=3D"color: #000000; text-decoratio=
n: none !important; border-bottom-width: 1px; border-bottom-color: #000000;=
 border-bottom-style: solid; background-color: #ccc;"> ever actually done i=
t</a>, and as far as I know whoever used to pretend to do it has stopped.=
=C2=A0</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">Anyway here=E2=80=99s a worse job:</p>
<blockquote><p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">An attorney for Musk,=C2=A0Alex Sp=
iro, said that Musk is =E2=80=9Cregularly and randomly drug tested at Space=
X and has never failed a test.=E2=80=9D=C2=A0</p></blockquote>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">Not Alex Spiro=E2=80=99s job, I mean; Alex Spi=
ro seems to be having fun. But imagine being the SpaceX employee in charge =
of randomly drug testing Elon Musk. Tiptoe=C2=A0into Musk=E2=80=99s office =
after his night out <a href=3D"https://link.mail.bloombergbusiness.com/clic=
k/33930957.258410/aHR0cHM6Ly93d3cudmljZS5jb20vZW4vYXJ0aWNsZS95M3ZqcGIvZWxvb=
i1tdXNrLWJlcmdoYWluLXJlZnVzZXMtZW50cnk/607f07ceef4b8524a319a23cBb0108ea8" i=
temprop=3D"StoryLink" itemscope=3D"itemscope" target=3D"_blank" style=3D"co=
lor: #000000; text-decoration: none !important; border-bottom-width: 1px; b=
order-bottom-color: #000000; border-bottom-style: solid; background-color: =
#ccc;"> not getting into Berghain</a>=C2=A0and say =E2=80=9Chey=C2=A0Mr. Mu=
sk it=E2=80=99s time for your random drug test, here=E2=80=99s a cup.=E2=80=
=9D What if he says no? What if he hands you back the cup and it is just fu=
ll of cocaine?=C2=A0What are you going to do about it? You work for him and=
 he is not, like, a chill and understanding guy.</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">Spiro=E2=80=99s non-denial<a class=3D"footnote=
-index" href=3D"#footnote-1" style=3D"color: #000000; text-decoration: none=
 !important; border-bottom-width: 1px; border-bottom-color: #000000; border=
-bottom-style: none !important; background-color: transparent !important; d=
isplay: inline-block;">
<span>[1]</span>
</a>=C2=A0comes from <a href=3D"https://link.mail.bloombergbusiness.com/cli=
ck/33930957.258410/aHR0cHM6Ly93d3cud3NqLmNvbS9idXNpbmVzcy9lbG9uLW11c2staWxs=
ZWdhbC1kcnVncy1lODI2YTllMT9tb2Q9aHBfbGVhZF9wb3Mx/607f07ceef4b8524a319a23cBc=
c03f479" itemprop=3D"StoryLink" itemscope=3D"itemscope" target=3D"_blank" s=
tyle=3D"color: #000000; text-decoration: none !important; border-bottom-wid=
th: 1px; border-bottom-color: #000000; border-bottom-style: solid; backgrou=
nd-color: #ccc;"> this Wall Street Journal story</a> about how Elon Musk =
=E2=80=9Chas used LSD, cocaine, ecstasy and psychedelic mushrooms,=E2=80=9D=
 as well as using ketamine recreationally, that =E2=80=9Chis drug use is on=
going, especially his consumption of ketamine,=E2=80=9D that people close t=
o him =E2=80=9Care concerned it could cause a health crisis,=E2=80=9D and t=
hat =E2=80=9Cillegal drug use would likely be a violation of federal polici=
es that could jeopardize SpaceX=E2=80=99s billions of dollars in government=
 contracts.=E2=80=9D</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">I actually doubt that last part? I feel like E=
lon Musk=E2=80=99s recent career is a long experiment to prove that, if you=
 are successful enough, the regular laws do not apply to you. I assume that=
 if Musk walked into the office of the secretary of defense and snorted a b=
ag of coke in front of him, no government contracts would be canceled. =E2=
=80=9CDo you want to send up your satellites on my good rockets, or do you =
want to enforce your rules about drug use by government contractors,=E2=80=
=9D Musk is implicitly asking, and there is an obviously correct answer.=C2=
=A0Musk is <a href=3D"https://link.mail.bloombergbusiness.com/click/3393095=
7.258410/aHR0cHM6Ly93d3cubmV3eW9ya2VyLmNvbS9tYWdhemluZS8yMDIzLzA4LzI4L2Vsb2=
4tbXVza3Mtc2hhZG93LXJ1bGU/607f07ceef4b8524a319a23cB61ab218b" itemprop=3D"St=
oryLink" itemscope=3D"itemscope" target=3D"_blank" style=3D"color: #000000;=
 text-decoration: none !important; border-bottom-width: 1px; border-bottom-=
color: #000000; border-bottom-style: solid; background-color: #ccc;">too bi=
g to fail</a> a drug test.</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">But Musk is also the chief executive officer o=
f a public company, Tesla Inc., and you have to feel for Tesla=E2=80=99s bo=
ard of directors:</p>
<ol style=3D"list-style-type: decimal; padding-left: 40px; margin: 16px 0;"=
>=09<li style=3D"margin-bottom: 5px;">On the one hand, Tesla does have poli=
cies against illegal drug use, and you could concoct a scenario in which Mu=
sk=E2=80=99s alleged drug use could somehow harm Tesla, either because it g=
ets him in trouble with customers or regulators or just because being on dr=
ugs all the time makes him an erratic decision maker.=C2=A0</li>=09<li styl=
e=3D"margin-bottom: 5px;">On the other hand, what are you gonna do about it=
? Fire him? That=E2=80=99s much worse for Tesla, probably. Ask him to stop?=
 Good luck with that.</li>
</ol>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">One good actual answer to =E2=80=9Cwhat are yo=
u gonna do about it=E2=80=9D is =E2=80=9Cquit=E2=80=9D:</p>
<blockquote><p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">One former Tesla director, Linda J=
ohnson Rice, grew so frustrated with Musk=E2=80=99s volatile behavior and h=
er concerns about his drug consumption that she didn=E2=80=99t stand for re=
-election to the electric-car company=E2=80=99s board in 2019, according to=
 people familiar with the matter.</p></blockquote>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">Reasonable. The other answer is =E2=80=9Ctalk =
about it in hushed, worried tones,=E2=80=9D which is fine for talking about=
 your friend=E2=80=99s drug use, but actually legally problematic for a pub=
lic company board of directors. The correct version of that answer is =E2=
=80=9Ctalk about it in hushed, worried tones, but not in a way that will ma=
ke it into any official board minutes that are later discoverable in litiga=
tion=E2=80=9D:</p>
<blockquote>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">Some Tesla board members over the years have t=
alked among themselves about their concerns over Musk=E2=80=99s alleged dru=
g use but haven=E2=80=99t said anything formally that would end up as an of=
ficial board agenda item or in meeting minutes, people familiar with the di=
scussions said. Some directors, including current Tesla board chair=C2=A0Ro=
byn Denholm, have gone to Kimbal Musk, who is a Tesla board member and was =
a SpaceX board member until early 2022, for help with Musk=E2=80=99s behavi=
or, without using the word =E2=80=9Cdrugs,=E2=80=9D the people said. =E2=80=
=A6</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">At Tesla, Denholm, the current board chair, Ja=
mes Murdoch and other directors sometimes gathered around Kimbal Musk infor=
mally during board breaks or after meetings to ask how Elon Musk was doing =
or if he was getting enough sleep, people familiar with the conversations s=
aid. While the directors wouldn=E2=80=99t specifically ask about substance =
abuse, the people said they understood the questions to be about Elon Musk=
=E2=80=99s perceived drug use.=C2=A0</p>
</blockquote>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">I wish that was a risk factor in the annual re=
port.<a class=3D"footnote-index" href=3D"#footnote-2" style=3D"color: #0000=
00; text-decoration: none !important; border-bottom-width: 1px; border-bott=
om-color: #000000; border-bottom-style: none !important; background-color: =
transparent !important; display: inline-block;">
<span>[2]</span>
</a>=C2=A0=E2=80=9CWe depend on the services of Elon Musk, our CEO and Tech=
noking, and we are=C2=A0<em>worried=C2=A0</em>that he isn=E2=80=99t getting=
 enough=C2=A0<em>sleep</em>, if you know what we mean. If he=C2=A0<em>keeps=
 staying up too late</em>, that may impact our business and financial resul=
ts.=E2=80=9D</p>
