<h2 style=3D"font-weight: bold; font-family: &quot;Arial Black&quot;, Arial=
, Helvetica, sans-serif; letter-spacing: -1px; font-size: 20px; border-bott=
om-width: 1px; border-bottom-style: dotted; margin: 0px; padding: 16px 0px =
5px;">Carta</h2>
</td>
</tr>
</table>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">The paradigmatic 21st century business model i=
s probably giving a product away for free, or at least below cost, in order=
 to collect data that can be used for lucrative targeted advertising. This =
is how=C2=A0most email=C2=A0works, and basically all of social media, and i=
t has become such a staple of modern business thought that companies like <=
a href=3D"https://link.mail.bloombergbusiness.com/click/33930957.258410/aHR=
0cHM6Ly93d3cuY2JpbnNpZ2h0cy5jb20vcmVzZWFyY2gvcmVwb3J0L2hvdy13ZXdvcmstbWFrZX=
MtbW9uZXkv/607f07ceef4b8524a319a23cB3c9f22cc" itemprop=3D"StoryLink" itemsc=
ope=3D"itemscope" target=3D"_blank" style=3D"color: #000000; text-decoratio=
n: none !important; border-bottom-width: 1px; border-bottom-color: #000000;=
 border-bottom-style: solid; background-color: #ccc;"> WeWork</a> and <a hr=
ef=3D"https://link.mail.bloombergbusiness.com/click/33930957.258410/aHR0cHM=
6Ly93d3cuYmxvb21iZXJnLmNvbS9vcGluaW9uL2FydGljbGVzLzIwMjItMTEtMDcvbW92aWVwYX=
NzLXdhcy1ub3QtYS1nb29kLWJ1c2luZXNzP2NtcGlkPUJCRDAxMDgyNF9NT05FWVNUVUZGJnV0b=
V9tZWRpdW09ZW1haWwmdXRtX3NvdXJjZT1uZXdzbGV0dGVyJnV0bV90ZXJtPTI0MDEwOCZ1dG1f=
Y2FtcGFpZ249bW9uZXlzdHVmZg/607f07ceef4b8524a319a23cB3c8bb771" itemprop=3D"S=
toryLink" itemscope=3D"itemscope" target=3D"_blank" style=3D"color: #000000=
; text-decoration: none !important; border-bottom-width: 1px; border-bottom=
-color: #000000; border-bottom-style: solid; background-color: #ccc;">  Mov=
iePass</a> could go around being like =E2=80=9Csure we charge people below =
our cost for office space or movie tickets, but see we collect=C2=A0<em>dat=
a</em>.=E2=80=9D</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">One problem with this model is that=C2=A0the b=
etter the data =E2=80=94=C2=A0the more intimate and valuable the informatio=
n you collect about your customers =E2=80=94=C2=A0the more annoyed people w=
ill get if you use it. When the ads are too targeted, it=E2=80=99s creepy a=
nd people get angry.</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">For instance, one product where this model see=
ms lucrative but tricky=C2=A0is startup cap table management:</p>
<ol style=3D"list-style-type: decimal; padding-left: 40px; margin: 16px 0;"=
>=09<li style=3D"margin-bottom: 5px;">Private companies issue shares to var=
ious people (founders, employees, contractors, angel investors, venture cap=
italists, etc.), with various terms and restrictions. The company needs to =
keep track of its capitalization table=C2=A0=E2=80=94=C2=A0who owns shares,=
 what sorts of shares they own, what restrictions they have, etc. =E2=80=94=
 in a robust, reliable, trustworthy way. It probably doesn=E2=80=99t have t=
he expertise to do that itself. And if you mess this up you get in bad trou=
ble.</li>=09<li style=3D"margin-bottom: 5px;">So there are companies =E2=80=
=94=C2=A0Carta is the main one =E2=80=94=C2=A0in the business of keeping th=
ese lists (startups=E2=80=99 capitalization tables) in reliable and user-fr=
iendly ways.</li>=09<li style=3D"margin-bottom: 5px;">Those lists are=C2=A0=
<em>so valuable</em>. Lots of investment bankers, wealth managers and other=
 intermediaries and service providers would absolutely=C2=A0<em>kill=C2=A0<=
/em>to know, for instance, the names and holdings of every Stripe or SpaceX=
 or OpenAI shareholder.<a class=3D"footnote-index" href=3D"#footnote-3" sty=
le=3D"color: #000000; text-decoration: none !important; border-bottom-width=
: 1px; border-bottom-color: #000000; border-bottom-style: none !important; =
background-color: transparent !important; display: inline-block;">
<span>[3]</span>
</a>=C2=A0Tons of things you can do with those=C2=A0lists.=C2=A0Most notabl=
y, a lot of outsiders want to=C2=A0<em>buy=C2=A0</em>shares of hot startups=
, but they can=E2=80=99t; those shares don=E2=80=99t trade in any sort of o=
rganized market. But=C2=A0if you know who owns the shares, you can call the=
m up, see who wants to sell, and then advertise=C2=A0=E2=80=9Chey I=E2=80=
=99ve got some Stripe shares for sale=E2=80=9D to the potential buyers. Sta=
rtup shares do not trade in a transparent way, and if you know who owns the=
 shares then you can make a killing as a broker.=C2=A0</li>
</ol>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">So from first principles it is tempting to, li=
ke, (1) build a great cap table management system, (2) go out to startups t=
o sign them up and (3) have a click-through user agreement where on screen=
=C2=A017 it is like =E2=80=9Cyou authorize us to use your cap table data in=
 any way that we want, including calling up your shareholders to pitch them=
 on trades.=E2=80=9D</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">This is, however, not how the cap table busine=
ss usually goes. In fact the shareholders don=E2=80=99t seem to want their =
data used this way, and neither do the companies. And this is a sensitive e=
nough issue that the companies are not going to just sign a click-through u=
ser agreement; they will actually say to the cap table company =E2=80=9Cyou=
 will keep our shareholder list confidential right?=E2=80=9D and the cap ta=
ble company will have to say yes.</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">Also, having the list is not the only impedime=
nt to startup share trading: Often startups prohibit their shareholders fro=
m selling, or have approval and/or first refusal rights over any sales. So =
if you had the cap table, you would look at it and see that everyone was re=
stricted from trading, so you couldn=E2=80=99t really use it to put togethe=
r trades anyway.</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">Startups care about keeping control over their=
 shareholder lists; the cap table management product is a tool for them to =
exercise that control. If a cap table management company=C2=A0<em>takes tha=
t control away from them </em>=E2=80=94=C2=A0if it uses its data to broker =
trades the company doesn=E2=80=99t want =E2=80=94=C2=A0then=C2=A0that=E2=80=
=99s bad service.=C2=A0</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">Still you see the appeal. Carta got in trouble=
 this weekend,=C2=A0Axios=E2=80=99s <a href=3D"https://link.mail.bloombergb=
usiness.com/click/33930957.258410/aHR0cHM6Ly93d3cuYXhpb3MuY29tL25ld3NsZXR0Z=
XJzL2F4aW9zLXByby1yYXRhLTM4YjQ3NWVlLWRlMjgtNDljOC1hNjJkLWIwNWYyNzNjNThjMS5o=
